The paper discusses the technical challenges associated with identifying and mitigating fake news, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques (cs.CL). It also mentions the impact of fake news on society and the need for interdisciplinary solutions, which falls under the category of social and information sciences (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the use of datasets for training and evaluation, which could be relevant to cyber security (cs.CR) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper mentions the use of social media platforms for the spread of fake news, which could be relevant to cybernetics (cs.CY).
